HEADWORD: Petaloideous
<hw>Pet`al*oid"e*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having the whole or part of the perianth petaline.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Petaloideous division</b></col>, <cd>that division of
endogenous plants in which the perianth is wholly or partly petaline,
embracing the <fam>Liliace⟦ae⟧</fam>, <fam>Orchidace⟦ae⟧</fam>,
<fam>Amaryllide⟦ae⟧</fam>, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petalosticha</ent>⟦br⟧
